41 class ChemNonEqStateModel : public StateModel
42 {
43 public:
44 
45  ChemNonEqStateModel(const Thermodynamics& thermo)
46  : StateModel(thermo, 1, thermo.nSpecies())
47  {
48  mp_work = new double [thermo.nSpecies()];
49  }
50 
51  ~ChemNonEqStateModel()
52  {
53  delete [] mp_work;
54  }
55 
63  void setState(
64  const double* const p_mass, const double* const p_energy,
65  const int vars = 0)
66  {
67  const int ns = m_thermo.nSpecies();
68 
69  // Compute the species concentrations which are used throughout this
70  // method regardless of variable set. Note that in the case where
71  // the p_mass vector is mass fractions, this is just dividing by the
72  // molecular weights as the first step in converting to mole fractions.
73  double conc = 0.0;
74  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i) {
75  // Check that species densities are at least positive
76  assert(p_mass[i] >= 0.0);
77  mp_X[i] = std::max(p_mass[i] / m_thermo.speciesMw(i), 0.0);
78  conc += mp_X[i];
79  }
80 
81  // Compute the temperature and pressure and make sure the variable set
82  // is implemented
83  switch (vars) {
84  case 0:
85  // Solve energy equation for temperature
86  getTFromRhoE(
87  Cp(m_thermo), H(m_thermo), p_energy[0], m_T, mp_work, -conc);
88  m_P = RU * m_T * conc;
89  break;
90 
91  case 1:
92  // Check that temperature is at least positive
93  assert(p_energy[0] > 0.0 && "Temperature is negative!");
94  m_T = p_energy[0];
95  m_P = RU * m_T * conc;
96  break;
97 
98  case 2:
99  // Check temperature and pressure are positive
100  assert(p_energy[0] > 0.0 && "Pressure is negative!");
101  assert(p_energy[1] > 0.0 && "Temperature is negative!");
102  m_P = p_energy[0];
103  m_T = p_energy[1];
104  break;
105 
106  default:
107  throw InvalidInputError("variable set", vars)
108  << "This variable-set is not implemented in ChemNonEqStateModel"
109  << ". Possible variable-sets are:\n"
110  << " 0: (species densities, static energy density)\n"
111  << " 1: (species densities, temperature)\n"
112  << " 2: (species mass fractions, pressure and temperature)";
113  }
114 
115  // All other temperatures are the same
116  m_Tr = m_Tv = m_Tel = m_Te = m_T;
117 
118  // Compute the species mole fractions
119  for (int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
120  mp_X[i] /= conc;
121  }
122 
123  void getTemperatures(double* const p_T) const {
124  p_T[0] = m_T;
125  }
126 
127  void getEnergiesMass(double* const p_e)
128  {
129  const int ns = m_thermo.nSpecies();
130  m_thermo.speciesHOverRT(mp_work);
131 
132  for(int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
133  p_e[i] = (mp_work[i] - 1.0)*m_T*RU/m_thermo.speciesMw(i);
134  }
135 
136  void getEnthalpiesMass(double* const p_h)
137  {
138  const int ns = m_thermo.nSpecies();
139  m_thermo.speciesHOverRT(mp_work);
140 
141  for(int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
142  p_h[i] = mp_work[i]*m_T*RU/m_thermo.speciesMw(i);
143  }
144 
145  void getCpsMass(double* const p_Cp)
146  {
147  const int ns = m_thermo.nSpecies();
148  m_thermo.speciesCpOverR(m_T, mp_work);
149 
150  for(int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
151  p_Cp[i] = mp_work[i]*RU/m_thermo.speciesMw(i);
152  }
153 
154  void getCvsMass(double* const p_Cv)
155  {
156  const int ns = m_thermo.nSpecies();
157  m_thermo.speciesCpOverR(m_T, mp_work);
158 
159  for(int i = 0; i < ns; ++i)
160  p_Cv[i] = (mp_work[i]-1.0)*RU/m_thermo.speciesMw(i);
161  }
162 
163 private:
164 
169  class Cp {
170  public:
171  Cp(const Thermodynamics& t) : thermo(t) {}
172  void operator () (double T, double* const cp) const {
173  thermo.speciesCpOverR(T, cp);
174  }
175  private:
176  const Thermodynamics& thermo;
177  };
178 
179 
184  class H {
185  public:
186  H(const Thermodynamics& t) : thermo(t) {}
187  void operator () (double T, double* const h) const {
188  thermo.speciesHOverRT(T, h);
189  }
190  private:
191  const Thermodynamics& thermo;
192  };
